sentences: Strut released his first demo, Rock On in 1993.
In 1999, he joined up with fellow hip hop emcee, Trem One, to record "Basic Fundamentals", which was released on Trem's second 12", Amateurs, by Unkut Recordings.
The group appeared on Culture of Kings Volume 1 (2000) with their track "Lyrical Mongrels".
Strut's debut solo album, The Authentic LP, was released in 2001 on the Obese Records label.
The track, "A Good Thing" appeared on Jurassic 5 DJ Nu-Mark's 2004 album, Hand's On, released by Sequence Records.
In 2002, Strut, in collaboration with Chopper Read, Bias B and Bob Balans, released a song called "Machete" on the Obesecity compilation album by various Australian hip hop artists.
In 2006 Strut released Legendary: The Official Mixtape on his newly formed Peruvian Gemz imprint, a subsidiary of Unkut Recordings.
2007 saw the release of Strut's second studio album, Legend: Official.
He played in Europe including Austria, Edinburgh Festival (2007) and Hip Hop Kemp (2006, 2008) in Czech Republic.
In 2009, Strut released a package set including Fallout Shelter EP and the Rejuvination LP whilst living in North London, UK.

Brad Strut was born in Yarrawonga in the Victorian countryside, and moved to Melbourne when he was nine years old.
He grew up in the Western suburbs and later in the inner Eastern suburbs of Melbourne.
